### Fase 2: Activación del Density Guard Real-time (Lógica de Dominio)

**Objetivo:** Transformar la validación de "log-only" a "bloqueo activo" con 3 capas de protección.

---

#### [MODIFY] [inventory.py (servicio)](file:///c:/API/interno/backend/inventory_service/inventory_app/services/inventory.py#L26-L36)

Reemplazar el método `_check_location_capacity` pasivo por la versión industrial:

```python
async def _check_location_capacity(self, warehouse_id, location_code, quantity, company_id, 
                                     product_weight_kg=None, product_volume_cm3=None,
                                     user_role="OPERATOR"):
    """
    [Phase 83] Active Density Guard: Triple-Layer Validation.
    """
    location = await self.repository.get_location_entity(warehouse_id, location_code, company_id)
    if not location:
        return  # Locaciones no registradas = sin límite (backwards compatible)

    # Layer 1: Validación de Unidades
    if location.max_capacity_units > 0:
        projected = location.current_units + quantity
        if projected > location.max_capacity_units:
            if user_role != "WAREHOUSE_MANAGER":
                raise ValueError("ERR_LOCATION_OVERFLOW_UNITS")
            # Manager override: registrar auditoría
            logger.warning(f"DENSITY_OVERRIDE: Manager authorized overflow at {location_code}")

    # Layer 2: Validación de Peso (Seguridad Industrial)
    if location.max_weight_kg > 0 and product_weight_kg:
        projected_weight = location.current_weight_kg + (product_weight_kg * quantity)
        if projected_weight > location.max_weight_kg:
            raise ValueError("ERR_LOCATION_OVERFLOW_WEIGHT")  # Sin override (seguridad)

    # Layer 3: Validación Volumétrica
    if location.volume_cm3 > 0 and product_volume_cm3:
        projected_volume = product_volume_cm3 * quantity
        # Solo warning por ahora (data de volumen de productos aún incompleta)
        if projected_volume > location.volume_cm3:
            logger.warning(f"DENSITY_VOLUME_WARNING: {location_code} projected overflow")
```

